#### Marine Corps Line Scores
The Marine Corps computes its three line scores for job qualification by adding scores from various ASVAB subtests. This method is crucial to determine an individual's qualifications for specific jobs within the Marine Corps.

:p What are the components used to calculate the General Technical (GT) line score in the Marine Corps?
??x
To calculate the General Technical (GT) line score, the Marine Corps uses the standard scores from Verbal Expression (VE) and Arithmetic Reasoning (AR). The formula is:
\[ GT = VE + AR \]
This combination helps evaluate a candidate's verbal reasoning and mathematical abilities.

```java
// Example Java code to calculate the General Technical (GT) line score
public class MarineCorpsLineScore {
    public int calculateGeneralTechnicalScore(int verbalExpression, int arithmeticReasoning) {
        return verbalExpression + arithmeticReasoning;
    }
}
```
