#### CAT-ASVAB Test Format and Constraints
Background context: The Computerized Adaptive Testing (CAT) version of the ASVAB has specific constraints related to time, marking answers, and tryout questions. Understanding these can help test-takers manage their time effectively.

:p What are some unique features of the CAT-ASVAB that distinguish it from the paper-and-pencil (P&P) version?
??x
Some unique features include:
1. You cannot go back to change or check your answers after completing a subtest.
2. Tryout questions, which do not affect your score but can extend test time.

For managing these constraints, it's crucial to pace yourself and use the tryout questions wisely if available.

```java
// Pseudocode for CAT-ASVAB Time Management Strategy
public void manageCATTime() {
    // Monitor the clock closely during each subtest.
    System.out.println("Starting Subtest: Please be mindful of time limits.");

    // If you're unsure about an answer, mark it and move on.
    if (unsureAboutAnswer) {
        markQuestion();
        continueTest();
    }

    // Use tryout questions effectively but note that they don't affect your score.
    if (tryoutAvailable()) {
        attemptTryoutQuestions();
    }
}
```
