#### P&P ASVAB Test Format and Constraints
Background context: The paper-and-pencil version of the ASVAB offers different advantages over the CAT-ASVAB, including the ability to skip questions, revisit them later, and change answers within a subtest.

:p What are some key differences between the paper-and-pencil (P&P) ASVAB and the Computerized Adaptive Testing (CAT) ASVAB?
??x
Key differences include:
1. **Skipping Questions**: In P&P, you can skip questions and revisit them later.
2. **Answer Change Flexibility**: You can change your answers within a subtest but not after time has expired in CAT-ASVAB.
3. **Marking Notes**: You may make notes on scratch paper in P&P but not directly on the answer sheet.

These differences can significantly impact test-taking strategy and pacing.

```java
// Pseudocode for Managing P&P ASVAB
public void managePnPTime() {
    // Note: Skip questions if you're unsure.
    if (unsureAnswer) {
        skipQuestion();
        rememberToReturnLater();
    }

    // Make temporary notes on scratch paper.
    makeNotesOnScratchPaper("Remember to check Q23 later");
}
```
