#### Harder Questions in Paper-Based Test
Background context: In the paper-based version of the ASVAB, harder questions are interspersed with easier ones. This can lead to spending excessive time on difficult questions and missing out on simpler ones at the end.

:p How does the intermingling of question difficulty levels impact test-takers during the P&P ASVAB?
??x
Intermingling hard and easy questions impacts test-takers as follows:
1. **Time Management Challenges**: Test-takers may spend too much time on difficult questions, potentially missing out on easier ones at the end.
2. **Score Implications**: This can lower overall scores if harder questions are not answered correctly.

To manage this effectively, it's important to pace yourself and skip hard questions temporarily to return to them later if time allows.

```java
// Pseudocode for Managing Question Difficulty Levels in P&P ASVAB
public void manageQuestionDifficulty() {
    // Monitor your progress.
    System.out.println("Time remaining: 30 minutes");

    // If a question is too difficult, mark it and return to it later if time permits.
    if (questionIsTooHard) {
        markQuestion();
        continueTestLater();
    }
}
```
