#### Time Management for Paper-and-Pencil ASVAB
Background context explaining the specific time limits and number of questions in the paper-and-pencil version. The test allows more time but requires careful pacing to ensure all sections are completed.

:p How much time do I have to answer questions on the paper-and-pencil version?
??x
On the paper-and-pencil version of the ASVAB, you have 11 minutes to answer 35 questions. This means you should aim for about 18 seconds per question (refer back to Chapter 6 if needed).

Example: 
```java
// Time management example
public class ASVBPTimeManagement {
